CAMH sid issue

Author

Santiago Sotelo

Published

March 5, 2023

Problem

  • In communication with Alexander Daros from CAMH Institute, it is informed that there is a problem with sid code of some users that are been defaulted to null

Objectives

  1. Identify the CAMH observation with sid defaulted to null and other problems in sid variable.

For the purpose of this report, we are going to use the data from BecharaReport API gathered in 2023-03-04. This data has 1’780’739 observations and 80 variables, and can be found in the following Dropbox path:

Mobio Interactive Dropbox/Research/RWD/Shared R Scripts/Input csv/BecharaReportFull-2023-03-04T05_15_17.csv

After applying the procedure to reduce the number of duplicates in the data, we have 71’897 observations in data.

Let’s enumerate the issues with CAMH sid variable:

Alex already identified half of CAMH users with null sid, using coupon_code variable, and provided the following conversion:
